ed_at":"2015-12-20T19:16:35.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7824#issuecomment-166148194","id":166148194,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7824","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2NjE0ODE5NA==","updated_at":"2015-12-20T19:16:35.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/166148194","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"So the `clone` method is being inherited from the prototypal chain\n\n`BoxHelper` -> `LineSegments` -> `Line` -> `Object3d`\n\nand it works by simply creating a new instance of that object's constructor, passing in `geometry` and `material` from that object.\n\nThe problem is, while most of these objects have a constructor pattern of `(geometry, material)` the helper constructors have a pattern of `(object3d)`.\n\nIn any case, the fix is to create a new clone method at the `*Helper` level that returns a new object using the `LineSegments` constructor.\n","created_at":"2015-12-20T19:18:03.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7824#issuecomment-166148262","id":166148262,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7824","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2NjE0ODI2Mg==","updated_at":"2015-12-20T19:18:03.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/166148262","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1349865?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/dhritzkiv","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzNDk4NjU=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"dhritzkiv","type":"User","id":1349865,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@WestLangley is the `update` line necessary? Won't a copy of `box` already reflect the boundingBox properties of `mesh` (unless `mesh` has somehow been transformed or morphed \u2013\u00a0something the code at r71 never dealt with)?\n","created_at":"2015-12-20T19:21:53.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7824#issuecomment-166148417","id":166148417,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7824","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2NjE0ODQxNw==","updated_at":"2015-12-20T19:21:53.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/166148417","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1349865?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/dhritzkiv","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzNDk4NjU=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"dhritzkiv","type":"User","id":1349865,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> @WestLangley is the update line necessary?\n\nIt was in my test. I created the mesh and helper prior to the first render.\n\n> In any case, the fix is to create a new clone method at the *Helper level that returns a new object using the LineSegments constructor.\n\nWell-stated. Would you be willing to file a PR to fix the helpers?\n","created_at":"2015-12-20T19:25:56.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7824#issuecomment-166148574","id":166148574,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7824","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2NjE0ODU3NA==","updated_at":"2015-12-20T19:25:56.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/166148574","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@WestLangley \n\n> > @WestLangley is the update line necessary?\n> \n> It was in my test. I created the mesh and helper prior to the first render.\n\nYou're right. I didn't notice that it wasn't working (it just wasn't breaking). That being said, instead of calling `helper1.update( mesh )`, I propose we effectively call `helper1.update( helper )`, since we aren't explicitly storing a reference to the `mesh` object, and using `helper` (that was derived from `mesh`) should give us the desired results.\n\n> Well-stated. Would you be willing to file a PR to fix the helpers?\n\nYes. I should have mentioned that I'm already working on a PR. I'm looking into creating a BaseHelper object that contains a clone method like this:\n\n``` js\n\nBaseHelper.prototype.clone = function clone() {\n\n    var clonedHelper = new THREE.LineSegments(this.geometry, this.material);\n    clonedHelper.update(this);\n    return clonedHelper;\n\n}\n\n```\n\nHowever, I'm not sure it will work, yet.\n","created_at":"2015-12-20T19:41:48.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7824#issuecomment-166149547","id":166149547,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7824","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2NjE0OTU0Nw==","updated_at":"2015-12-20T19:41:48.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/166149547","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1349865?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/dhritzkiv","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzNDk4NjU=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"dhritzkiv","type":"User","id":1349865,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dhritzkiv\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I believe `BoxHelper` is the only helper whose `update()` method requires an argument. To that end, we could change `BoxHelper`'s API if need be.\n","created_at":"2015-12-20T20:44:44.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7824#issuecomment-166152863","id":166152863,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7824","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2NjE1Mjg2Mw==","updated_at":"2015-12-20T20:44:44.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/166152863","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other